commitResults.messageBody:
Current Person attribute classes require each attribute to be populated
with information.

All attributes may not be available at time of insertion of contact.

Modify behavior such that attributes may be empty at time of insertion
of contact; allows contact to be created first and additional information
to be added later.

Let's,
* intergrate the GitHubProfile, Language classes into the Person class and
  modify the behavior of the Person class to allow late insertion of
  attribute information
* update the relevant tests to handle additional attributes, and changes
  to behavior

Add sort feature Add sort command to allow the sorting of the list of contacts.
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently the user is not able to sort the list of contacts.

The user may want to organize the list by sorting.

Let's
* add sort command that allows the sorting of the list by name, phone, email or address.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update sorts Update sorts to handle empty strings.
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the sort makes use of natural ordering which places empty string at the front of the list. This is counter intuitive to the purpose of organising the list based on a category.

The user would want contacts that does not have the specified category to be at the back.

Let's
* update sort in UniquePersonList to place empty strings last.

UniquePersonList.java:
* update comparators to position empty strings at the end.
